<DESCRIPT>  FASHION  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  EURO STYLE: Mary Hamilton, vice president and fashion director of Emporium,
will show slides and give an overview of the fall 1991 fashion shows in Milan,
London and Paris at the 6 p.m. Wednesday meeting of Fashion Group
International at the San Francisco Fashion Center, 699 Eighth St., San
Francisco. Tickets are $25 in advance, $30 at the door and $15 for students.
Information and reservations: (415) 254-1698.;    WINNING LOOKS:  San
Francisco-based Ruby Mann will hold a trunk show of its spring collection and
a preview of fall from 1 to 5 p.m. Saturday at Ralph Davies, 77 Maiden Lane,
San Francisco. Designers Ruth Stein and Naomi Mann, winners of the 1991 Focus
Magazine Rising Star Award, will be present. Information: (415) 397-3200.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  REVIEW OF FALL '91 FASHION SET IN S.F.  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Style Events  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     IMPACT:  Image consultant Marcie Hunt will teach a seminar for women on
"How to Build a Wardrobe With Impact and Style" from 10 a.m. to 1:30 p.m.
April 27 at Foothill College, 12345 El Monte Road, Los Altos Hills. Fee is
$45. Information and registration: (415) 949-7373.;    GREAT SPREADS:  "The
Great Quilt Revival: Quiltmaking Between Two World Wars 1918-1941" is on
exhibit through May 11 at the American Museum of Quilts &amp; Textiles, 766 S.
Second St., San Jose. More than 50 quilts are featured, including crib,
appliqued and pieced quilts as well as toys, books and dolls from the period.
The exhibit is open from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. Tuesdays through Saturdays and is
free. Information: (408) 971-0323.  </TEXT>
<BYLINE>  -- Mary Gottschalk  </BYLINE>
